{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":21965,"name":"","username":"nergal","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/7c8e57/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-11-24T18:00:17.610Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIs it possible to use Billboard without a BillboardSet and handle all Billboards manually?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAccording to the documentation it seems to require BillboardSet, but I‚Äôm not quite sure. At least it‚Äôs not possible to use Billboard as a component.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe reason I want to use Billboards without a set is because I want to have a dynamic sized set of Billboard and still be able to get the specific Billboard in the set by giving a predefined Index (such as a 3D array flatten as a 1D array).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSince a BillboardSet creates each Billboard beforehand it creates a lot of overhead memory wise.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-11-24T18:00:17.610Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":56,"reads":29,"readers_count":28,"score":290.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3776,"topic_slug":"using-billboard-outside-a-billboardset","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":825,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":21967,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2017-11-24T19:30:06.188Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"nergal\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"3776\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/7c8e57/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e nergal:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSince a BillboardSet creates each Billboard beforehand it creates a lot of overhead memory wise.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou are tryin‚Äô to do something unlogical. The main purpose of \u003ccode\u003eBillboardSet\u003c/code\u003e is to optimize things by grouping.\u003cbr\u003e\nYou would have x10 overhead if allocate billboards one by one e,g, in \u003ccode\u003eStaticModel\u003c/code\u003e. x100, if you create a lot of \u003ccode\u003eBillboardSet\u003c/code\u003es with single element.\u003cbr\u003e\nIf you want to have \u003cem\u003ea lot\u003c/em\u003e of billboards without pre-allocating storage, you could resize \u003ccode\u003eBillboardSet\u003c/code\u003e on demand or create a few of them to avoid buffers re-allocation.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-11-24T19:30:06.188Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":30,"readers_count":29,"score":26.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3776,"topic_slug":"using-billboard-outside-a-billboardset","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":fals